<div id="review_3625673617" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3625673617" />
    <a title="Denise &#39;     -      &#39; Lopez" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/101972507-denise---lopez"><img alt="Denise &#39;     -      &#39; Lopez" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1567293701p2/101972507.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3625673617?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Denise &#39;     -      &#39; Lopez" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Denise &#39;     -      &#39; Lopez" href="/user/show/101972507-denise---lopez">Denise &#39;     -      &#39; Lopez</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3625673617" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14384634343470749887">I&apos;ve actually read this book before, it was one of my favorites, and i just wanted to see if I would still like the book as much as I used to. Its an easy and fast read, but hinestly I think its very enjoyable no matter the age. The book is like a life lesson, don&apos;t give up on hope or on yourself. I think quite a few people have mentioned that the book is kind of like Toy story, and I agree, but I feel like even though the topic is very similar, this book still towers over toy story. When Edward</span>
  <span id="freeText14384634343470749887" style="display:none">I've actually read this book before, it was one of my favorites, and i just wanted to see if I would still like the book as much as I used to. Its an easy and fast read, but hinestly I think its very enjoyable no matter the age. The book is like a life lesson, don't give up on hope or on yourself. I think quite a few people have mentioned that the book is kind of like Toy story, and I agree, but I feel like even though the topic is very similar, this book still towers over toy story. When Edward is moved around he is by himself, in Toy Story friendship and teamwork is very incorporated. This book teaches that with love that comes, so does separation. Because good things end. Edward's character in general is really well fleshed out and we can feel his emotions. Now for one of the main reasons I love this book, the ending. Maybe it's just me, but I really didn't expect it. I got so attached to Edward that when he was under the weather I just wanted to do anything in my power to help(ahem...obviously I couldn't). I feel like I could've read 200 pages more on how he becomes happy once again, and he accepts the fact that not everything lasts, but we should make the most of it. Nothing has changed through all these years. This book is still great. Its really nostalgic. &gt;^&lt;</span>
  <a data-text-id="14384634343470749887" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


